{
  "description": "Locked-model declarations — ONE doc schema serving THREE named-parameter families (scent_model, wire_shape, info_mode). A peer publishes a doc, hashes it with the section-2 compact canonical form, and declares only the hash at negotiate time under '<family>_sha256'. The schema exists so that two teams' hashes are COMPARABLE: a bare hash over an ad-hoc dict makes two correct implementations of the same model refuse each other. Refusal fires ONLY when both peers declare a family and disagree — omission is never refusal. See SPEC section 7.",
  "doc_schema": {
    "keys": [
      "family",
      "name",
      "params",
      "example"
    ],
    "families": [
      "scent_model",
      "wire_shape",
      "info_mode"
    ],
    "hash": "sha256(canonical_json(doc))",
    "declared_key": "<family>_sha256"
  },
